00:04:48.500 --> 00:04:54.700
Let me just say a few words about
the work that Congressman Wolf

00:04:54.700 --> 00:04:59.380
and I did together
relative to our people.

00:04:59.380 --> 00:05:06.060
Back in 2008, we came together
and decided that there needed

00:05:06.060 --> 00:05:10.120
to be a vehicle recognized
in the House.

00:05:10.120 --> 00:05:17.160
And so we created a caucus that's
called the Religious Minorities

00:05:17.160 --> 00:05:18.970
in the Middle East Caucus.

00:05:18.970 --> 00:05:22.690
And we had at least
two goals in mind.

00:05:22.690 --> 00:05:27.640
First of all, we knew that members
of Congress needed to be educated.

00:05:27.640 --> 00:05:33.200
They knew very little or nothing,
and this is not fault or blame,

00:05:33.200 --> 00:05:36.550
they just didn't know,
they didn't understand.

00:05:36.550 --> 00:05:41.670
Some were even surprised, hold
on to your seats, or your hats,

00:05:41.670 --> 00:05:44.080
that there were Christians
in the Middle East.

00:05:44.080 --> 00:05:46.210
Imagine that.

00:05:46.210 --> 00:05:48.210
And one of my favorite
responses was,

00:05:48.210 --> 00:05:51.900
where do you think Jesus was
born, Trenton New Jersey?

00:05:51.900 --> 00:05:58.730
So that was one of our
goals, but also to deepen

00:05:58.730 --> 00:06:05.680
and broaden their appreciation
of the ancient cultures

00:06:05.680 --> 00:06:11.620
in the Middle East and why they
deserve our support in the Congress

00:06:11.620 --> 00:06:18.100
and the nexus between the values
of America that would drive us

00:06:18.100 --> 00:06:21.230
to do that, that would
drive us to do that.

00:06:21.230 --> 00:06:23.630
Clearly, there's a
nexus between them.

00:06:23.630 --> 00:06:28.680
Now, we only had a few members to
begin with but we kept working.

00:06:28.680 --> 00:06:31.850
I think two of the most
important accomplishments,

00:06:31.850 --> 00:06:40.460 position:56%
and I want to acknowledge again,
Congressman Wolf's just fearlessness

00:06:40.460 --> 00:06:50.010 position:56%
and insistence that we would secure
$10 million in 2010 to fund programs

00:06:50.010 --> 00:06:53.210
that would protect Iraq's
religious minorities,

00:06:53.210 --> 00:06:56.160 position:56%
and secondly, we passed legislation.

00:06:56.160 --> 00:07:01.370 position:56%
And it really was at his
insistence to create a special envoy

00:07:01.370 --> 00:07:04.110
for religious minorities
in the Middle East.

00:07:04.110 --> 00:07:06.590
I remember Frank saying
to me, "Anna,

00:07:06.590 --> 00:07:13.380
if there is not a point
person that is a high level,

00:07:13.380 --> 00:07:17.900
then we're just going to drift
from one person to another

00:07:17.900 --> 00:07:20.860
within the State Department."

00:07:20.860 --> 00:07:23.020
How right he was about that.

00:07:23.020 --> 00:07:24.930
So I think that we've
come a long way.

00:07:24.930 --> 00:07:29.770
The caucus is grown now to
over fifty active members

00:07:29.770 --> 00:07:35.950
and we've advanced, I think, very
recently an historic achievement.

00:07:35.950 --> 00:07:39.360
On March 14th of this year,
the United States House

00:07:39.360 --> 00:07:45.770
of Representatives
voted 393 to zero.

00:07:45.770 --> 00:07:47.090
So it was unanimous.

00:07:47.090 --> 00:07:53.160
Every member that was on the floor
to vote voted for the resolution

00:07:53.160 --> 00:07:58.500
that Congressman Jeff Fortenberry
and myself were the sponsors of.

00:07:58.500 --> 00:08:05.280 position:56%
He is now, he has taken Frank's
place as the Co-Chair of the caucus.

00:08:05.280 --> 00:08:07.480
Now, why is this historic?

00:08:07.480 --> 00:08:12.310
This is only the second time in
the history of the United States

00:08:12.310 --> 00:08:19.940
of America that as a genocide is
taking place, that we would place

00:08:19.940 --> 00:08:23.750
that definition on
what is occurring.

00:08:23.750 --> 00:08:26.820
The other was Rwanda.

00:08:28.120 --> 00:08:34.510
And it defines the persecution of
Christians, obviously Assyrians

00:08:34.510 --> 00:08:40.790 position:56%
because we are Christian, Chaldeans,
Syriacs, Yazidis and other ethnic

00:08:40.790 --> 00:08:44.830
and religious minorities
in Iraq and Syria.

00:08:44.830 --> 00:08:47.800
Three days later, imagine
this Frank,

00:08:47.800 --> 00:08:54.860
the State Department I think took a
historic step as well by asserting

00:08:54.860 --> 00:08:59.530
that the persecution
of Christians, Yazidis

00:08:59.530 --> 00:09:04.720
and by Isis is in fact a genocide.

00:09:04.720 --> 00:09:07.960
In a powerful, and I think
really poignant speech,

00:09:07.960 --> 00:09:11.420
the Secretary of State
stated "the fact

00:09:11.420 --> 00:09:13.750
that dioecious [assumed
spelling] kills Christians

00:09:13.750 --> 00:09:18.770 position:56%
because they are Christians,
Yazidis because they are as Yazidis,

00:09:18.770 --> 00:09:21.280
Shia because they are Shia.

00:09:21.280 --> 00:09:26.650
In its entire worldview, it's
based on eliminating those

00:09:26.650 --> 00:09:31.980
who do not subscribe to
its perverse ideology.

00:09:31.980 --> 00:09:36.040
There is no question in my
mind that if dioecius succeeded

00:09:36.040 --> 00:09:39.020
in establishing its
so-called caliphate,

00:09:39.020 --> 00:09:43.440
it would seek to destroy
what remains of ethnic

00:09:43.440 --> 00:09:48.740
and the religious mosaic which
once thrived in the region."

00:09:48.740 --> 00:09:52.800
And as I said, it's only the
second time in the history

00:09:52.800 --> 00:09:58.610
of the United States of America
that such a designation has been,

00:09:58.610 --> 00:10:00.240
the designation has been placed.

00:10:00.240 --> 00:10:07.260
But we still have an
enormous amount of work to do.

00:10:07.260 --> 00:10:13.690
Today, June 10th marks the second
anniversary of the invasion

00:10:13.690 --> 00:10:18.850
of Mosul, when half a million
people fled for their lives.

00:10:18.850 --> 00:10:24.460
Some didn't make it, and we
know what happened to them.

00:10:24.460 --> 00:10:28.930
Overnight, we saw the
systematic extermination

00:10:28.930 --> 00:10:32.940
of the world's oldest
Christian communities by Isis,

00:10:32.940 --> 00:10:35.440 position:56%
and of course, they haven't stopped.

00:10:35.440 --> 00:10:37.630
They continue to ravage Iraq

00:10:37.630 --> 00:10:41.200
and Syria's religious
and ethnic minorities.

00:10:41.200 --> 00:10:43.010
Men and boys are being killed,

00:10:43.010 --> 00:10:47.650
women and girls are being
abducted, sold, raped.

00:10:47.650 --> 00:10:51.130
So a genocide designation

00:10:51.130 --> 00:10:56.940 position:56%
by the United States is an important
step, but it's only one step.

00:10:56.940 --> 00:11:01.580
I work daily with my colleagues
both in the caucus and from

00:11:01.580 --> 00:11:06.640 position:56%
across the House of Representatives.

00:11:06.640 --> 00:11:10.050
This is a nonpartisan issue.

00:11:10.050 --> 00:11:12.950
This is not Republican, Democrat.

00:11:12.950 --> 00:11:15.890
We never treated it that way.

00:11:15.890 --> 00:11:20.340
It should not be treated that
way because we need to attract

00:11:20.340 --> 00:11:22.850
as much support as we can.

00:11:22.850 --> 00:11:30.860 position:56%
We're working on a daily basis to
continue to secure humanitarian aid.

00:11:30.860 --> 00:11:37.890
We work to bring about security
and an expedited pathway

00:11:37.890 --> 00:11:43.390
to refugee status for the besieged
ethnic and religious minorities

00:11:43.390 --> 00:11:48.380
in Iraq and Syria who are
just suffering so immensely

00:11:48.380 --> 00:11:57.110
that there are not adjectives I
think that fit the word suffering.

00:11:57.110 --> 00:12:01.280
We also continue to
assist USAID partners

00:12:01.280 --> 00:12:06.170
in reaching the displaced
populations, and Assyrians are

00:12:06.170 --> 00:12:12.760
so much a part of that, that reside
outside of the refugee camps.

00:12:12.760 --> 00:12:17.130
And we know very especially
that, that is,

00:12:17.130 --> 00:12:26.290
that that describes the Assyrians
and a majority obviously of those

00:12:26.290 --> 00:12:30.870
that are afraid to be in
the camps mixed with others

00:12:30.870 --> 00:12:34.640
because of a long and
troubled history.

00:12:34.640 --> 00:12:41.320
We're also working very hard
to see that as the areas

00:12:41.320 --> 00:12:46.480
that are liberated, that the
Kurdish regional government

00:12:46.480 --> 00:12:53.140
and the Iraqi government not
only honor the return for those

00:12:53.140 --> 00:12:59.010
that were forced to flee, but
also to have a safe haven,

00:12:59.010 --> 00:13:03.630
also to have a safe
haven because, well,

00:13:03.630 --> 00:13:06.120
