01:29:17.340 --> 01:29:21.680
at least one article that
specifically about that in Iran.

01:29:21.680 --> 01:29:27.960
But we have the rise of theater
performance in Tehran, in Baghdad

01:29:27.960 --> 01:29:30.600
and in Qamishli, Qamishli all
of you know is in Eastern Syria.

01:29:30.600 --> 01:29:36.590
In the United States because of
the large Diaspora following the

01:29:36.590 --> 01:29:44.340
genocide we have performances
of plays by non-professionals,

01:29:44.340 --> 01:29:47.060
non-professional communities,
social groups and so on.

01:29:47.060 --> 01:29:50.860
Especially along the East Coast
we have some wonderful wonderful

01:29:50.860 --> 01:29:54.440
pictures from that period
where they performed things

01:29:54.440 --> 01:29:55.870
like Arshin Mamalan
[assumed spelling]

01:29:55.870 --> 01:30:00.010
which is an Azarish Turkish
play that is very popular made

01:30:00.010 --> 01:30:02.740
into film four times
at least in Chicago

01:30:02.740 --> 01:30:06.270
and in the Central
Valley in the 1950s.

01:30:06.270 --> 01:30:11.610
In the USSR, the former Soviet
Union there was considerable state

01:30:11.610 --> 01:30:16.300
sponsorship of Assyrian
cultural activity.

01:30:16.300 --> 01:30:22.820
This is because the language of
the Assyrians was recognized as one

01:30:22.820 --> 01:30:25.800
of the nationality
languages of the Soviet Union.

01:30:25.800 --> 01:30:30.060
It came with that territoriality,
but where there were large clusters

01:30:30.060 --> 01:30:34.760
as in Armenia and in Georgia
they had schools of their own

01:30:34.760 --> 01:30:36.070
which was sponsored by the state.

01:30:36.070 --> 01:30:39.660
With the end of the Soviet Union
that kind of sponsorship has ended

01:30:39.660 --> 01:30:46.690
and the community in Russia and
in the Trans Caucasus is active

01:30:46.690 --> 01:30:48.840
but not as active as before.

01:30:48.840 --> 01:30:53.730
So in our time now, in the last
twenty years Europe and Australia

01:30:53.730 --> 01:30:57.560
and the United States have
become refugee locations

01:30:57.560 --> 01:31:00.800
but state sponsorship
of Assyrian activity,

01:31:00.800 --> 01:31:03.760
cultural activity is
very very limited.

01:31:03.760 --> 01:31:08.400
So the community has to depend
on itself, on its own resources

01:31:08.400 --> 01:31:11.840
in order to raise the funds
to be able to perform,

01:31:11.840 --> 01:31:15.650
to create any kind of
cultural performance.

01:31:15.650 --> 01:31:19.170
The content of the plays as I said

01:31:19.170 --> 01:31:21.210
from Arshin Mamalan [assumed
spelling] is an example.

01:31:21.210 --> 01:31:26.020
We also have examples of
adaptations of Russian material

01:31:26.020 --> 01:31:32.580 position:56%
and we have originals skits, plays
based on Assyrian historical events.

01:31:32.580 --> 01:31:35.870
A lot of this is not fully
documented, but there's a good deal

01:31:35.870 --> 01:31:38.960
of material on it that
we have published in some

01:31:38.960 --> 01:31:42.650
of the Assyrian organization
magazines

01:31:42.650 --> 01:31:48.860
such as the Assyrian Star
and these are available.

01:31:48.860 --> 01:31:52.030
Choral and solo singing
of art songs,

01:31:52.030 --> 01:31:55.100
especially in Tehran,
became very popular.

01:31:55.100 --> 01:32:01.060
The inspiration from music, my
eyes over there, the inspiration

01:32:01.060 --> 01:32:04.190
for music is incorporation

01:32:04.190 --> 01:32:08.040
of Assyrian traditional
melodies to Western instruments.

01:32:08.040 --> 01:32:13.430
So the three leading figures for
this kind of activity are all

01:32:13.430 --> 01:32:17.520
from Iran and as you
will see from this chart,

01:32:17.520 --> 01:32:22.750
two thirds have emigrated
and died in, in the West.

01:32:22.750 --> 01:32:28.690 position:56%
So what is happening then is that we
know for example that Assyrian music

01:32:28.690 --> 01:32:33.710
in the ancient period had certain
instruments that are depicted

01:32:33.710 --> 01:32:36.480
or known, and there are
some discussions of it

01:32:36.480 --> 01:32:39.650 position:56%
but there's also some music from the
Ancient period that is performed.

01:32:39.650 --> 01:32:43.880
So what happens is when we have
Assyrian affairs then we have say a

01:32:43.880 --> 01:32:47.270
harp substituting for what
would have been an Ancient

01:32:47.270 --> 01:32:49.410
Assyrian instrument.

01:32:49.410 --> 01:32:55.020
My emphasis for a bit of
this talk is going to be

01:32:55.020 --> 01:32:57.740
on the Mesopotamian night
